        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add QA evidence summary normalization",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a normalized QA evidence summary schema grouped by `test`, `mapping`, `execution`, and `result` so suite, live transport, Vitest, and Playwright proof can share one artifact shape without forcing everything into scenario terminology.\n- Keep taxonomy and mapping provenance out of the base evidence producer: evidence stores runnable-test identity, mapping relation IDs/refs, execution facts, artifacts, and result data; report/gate consumers join that through the checked-in taxonomy and mapping layers.\n- Treat evidence `profile` as an opaque mapping id in the artifact. The mapped runner/taxonomy stack validates runnable profile membership; the base evidence schema does not hardcode the profile list.\n- Embed the foundational `evidence` block in QA suite and Telegram live summaries without adding a release gate.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/evidence-summary.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.summary-json.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite-summary.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/telegram/telegram-live.runtime.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `git diff --check`\n- live PR diff/body check for personal-name owner references\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: QA Lab outputs now include a normalized evidence summary shape that can represent QA suite scenarios, live transport checks, Vitest tests, and Playwright tests.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw Codex worktree on macOS, with focused unit/schema tests.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran the focused evidence summary, suite summary JSON, suite summary rendering, and Telegram live runtime tests through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, plus whitespace and live PR diff/body checks.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused Vitest passed 4 files / 65 tests; `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` passed; `git diff --check` passed; the live PR diffs and bodies contain no personal-name owner references.\n\nObserved result after fix: Evidence entries are grouped as `test`, `mapping`, `execution`, and `result`. Mapping coverage rows keep relation role, surface/category IDs, and ref IDs; refs are normalized once under `mapping.refs`; execution contains provider/model, channel, runner, package source, environment, and artifact objects; result contains status, failure, and timing.\n\nWhat was not tested: No maturity or release gate was added or run, no channel-driver SDK lane was implemented, and no live Telegram provider lane was executed for this scoped schema/output-shape change.\n\n",
